# Hybrid OCR Pipeline Design — SnapBudget

## Understanding Summary

- **What**: A 3-mode OCR pipeline for receipt scanning in the SnapBudget Android app
- **Why**: Gives users control over privacy/accuracy tradeoff; enables offline-first with optional AI enhancement
- **Who**: SnapBudget users scanning Indian retail receipts
- **Current state**: ML Kit OCR + regex parsing + Gemini AI fallback (hardcoded, always-on when confidence < 0.6)
- **Constraint**: Android (Kotlin), must keep existing [OcrProcessor](file:///c:/Users/patil/AndroidStudioProjects/TEST/app/src/main/java/com/snapbudget/ocr/ocr/OcrProcessor.kt#14-80), [ReceiptParser](file:///c:/Users/patil/AndroidStudioProjects/TEST/app/src/main/java/com/snapbudget/ocr/ocr/ReceiptParser.kt#56-912), `ReceiptTypeClassifier` intact

## Three Modes

| Mode | OCR Engine | Parsing | Categorization | Network |
|------|-----------|---------|---------------|---------|
| **1 — Offline** | ML Kit (on-device) | [ReceiptParser](file:///c:/Users/patil/AndroidStudioProjects/TEST/app/src/main/java/com/snapbudget/ocr/ocr/ReceiptParser.kt#56-912) regex | `ReceiptTypeClassifier` TF-IDF | None |
| **2 — Hybrid** | ML Kit (on-device) | [ReceiptParser](file:///c:/Users/patil/AndroidStudioProjects/TEST/app/src/main/java/com/snapbudget/ocr/ocr/ReceiptParser.kt#56-912) regex | Groq AI for category + word correction | API call |
| **3 — Cloud AI** | Groq Vision API | Groq AI parses full receipt | Groq AI categorization | API call |

## Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  OcrPipelineMode (enum)               │
│          OFFLINE / HYBRID / CLOUD_AI                  │
└──────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘
               │
┌──────────────▼───────────────────────────────────────┐
│              OcrPipelineConfig (object)               │
│   - reads mode from SharedPreferences                │
│   - reads GROQ_API_KEY from BuildConfig (.env)       │
│   - validates: if no key → force OFFLINE             │
└──────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘
               │
┌──────────────▼───────────────────────────────────────┐
│           ReceiptProcessor (modified)                 │
│                                                       │
│  switch (mode) {                                     │
│    OFFLINE →                                         │
│      OcrProcessor(ML Kit) → ReceiptParser → done     │
│                                                       │
│    HYBRID →                                          │
│      OcrProcessor(ML Kit) → ReceiptParser            │
│      → GroqAiService.correctAndCategorize(rawText)   │
│      → merge AI results with parsed receipt          │
│                                                       │
│    CLOUD_AI →                                        │
│      GroqAiService.ocrAndParse(imageBytes)           │
│      → returns fully parsed receipt from AI          │
│  }                                                   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Switching Logic

```kotlin
// In ReceiptProcessor.processOcrResult()
when (OcrPipelineConfig.getMode(context)) {
    OFFLINE -> {
        // Current flow minus Gemini fallback
        // ReceiptParser + ReceiptTypeClassifier only
    }
    HYBRID -> {
        // Current flow, but replace Gemini with GroqAiService
        // AI called only when confidence < 0.6 or fields missing
        // AI corrects merchant names, amounts, and assigns category
    }
    CLOUD_AI -> {
        // Skip ML Kit entirely
        // Send image to Groq Vision API
        // AI returns structured JSON: merchant, amount, date, category, GST
    }
}
```

**Fallback rule**: If API call fails in HYBRID/CLOUD_AI → degrade to OFFLINE result silently.

## Groq AI Integration

### API Key Storage

```properties
# .env file (project root, gitignored)
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_xxxxxxxxxxxx
```

```kotlin
// build.gradle.kts — inject into BuildConfig
android {
    defaultConfig {
        val envFile = rootProject.file(".env")
        val groqKey = if (envFile.exists()) {
            envFile.readLines()
                .firstOrNull { it.startsWith("GROQ_API_KEY=") }
                ?.substringAfter("=")?.trim() ?: ""
        } else ""
        buildConfigField("String", "GROQ_API_KEY", "\"$groqKey\"")
    }
    buildFeatures { buildConfig = true }
}
```

### GroqAiService (new file, replaces GenerativeAiFallbackService)

```kotlin
// com.snapbudget.ocr.ocr.GroqAiService
class GroqAiService {
    private val apiKey = BuildConfig.GROQ_API_KEY
    private val endpoint = "https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions"
    private val model = "llama-3.3-70b-versatile"  // text tasks
    private val visionModel = "llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct"  // vision tasks

    // HYBRID mode: correct OCR text + categorize
    suspend fun correctAndCategorize(rawOcrText: String): AiResult?

    // CLOUD_AI mode: full receipt OCR from image
    suspend fun ocrAndParse(imageBase64: String): AiResult?

    data class AiResult(
        val merchantName: String?,
        val totalAmount: Double?,
        val date: String?,
        val gstNumber: String?,
        val category: String?,
        val confidence: Float
    )
}
```

### HTTP Implementation

Uses `java.net.HttpURLConnection` (no new dependencies):

```kotlin
private suspend fun callGroq(messages: List<Map<String, Any>>): String? =
    withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
        val conn = URL(endpoint).openConnection() as HttpURLConnection
        conn.requestMethod = "POST"
        conn.setRequestProperty("Authorization", "Bearer $apiKey")
        conn.setRequestProperty("Content-Type", "application/json")
        conn.doOutput = true
        // ... write JSON body, read response, parse content
    }
```

## Decision Log

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| Groq over Gemini | User-requested; fast inference, free tier available |
| `HttpURLConnection` over OkHttp | Zero new dependencies |
| SharedPreferences for mode | Already used (CategoryClassifier), simple toggle |
| BuildConfig for API key | Standard Android pattern, keeps key out of source |
| Silent fallback to OFFLINE | User should never see a broken scan |
| Keep existing parsers intact | Mode 1 & 2 still depend on them; proven accuracy |

